	<MenuItem id="moveDevBetweenBridges">
		<Name>Move Device(s) from one bridge to another...</Name>
		<ConfigUI>

			<Field type="label" id="instructions1">
				<Label>If you have moved lights/sensors to a new bridge  or migrated the bridge to a new pro bridge you can use this menue item.
It will keep the old indigo device (ID) and replace it with the properties of the new hue dev on the new bridge
Then it will delete the new indigo device, as the old device will have all the properties of the new device
This way you can keep names, triggers, actions, scripts, indigo ids etc
SEQUENCE:
1. if you just move a device: delete device on old bridge with the Hue app (not in indigo)
1a. if you migrate a bridge to the pro bridge, follow the migration steps and the switch off the old bridge
2. create new Hue device on new Hue bridge (with the Hue app or through migrating from old version bridge to pro version).
   Indigo will auto create the new device w new bridge number. 
   you will have one orphan (old) indigo device and one new indigo device
3. use this menu (old = device in indigo you want to keep)
- select bridge of old device
- select bridge of new device
- select device you want to keep OLD
- select device you want to copy NEW
== click execute
The OLD indigo device(-new aded to name) will point to the new device on the new Hue bridge and will have its properties copied
The NEW indigo device will be deleted in INDIGO 
  as it is a duplicate of the new-old one now, but with a new indigo ID

!!! make sure you select the right devices!!! 
It Does not work for different device types 
The plugin only performs a highlevel check on type of bulb/sensor/groups.

The device on the old hub will be ignored until you  reload the plugin.
After reload if the device still exists on the old bridge (and the bridge exists) 
 then the old device will be re-created again.
 you then must delete it on the hub or switch off the old bridge
</Label>
			</Field>

